snippet.textDisplay:
Awesome geet! Chaaran is a caste in rajasthan who where singers, writers, poets, music tellers as well as warriors in part. They mainly have records of Rajput history. There are claims that charans had their roots in rajputs only! 
There are chaarans still in rajasthan who have records of rajputana history! 


Charans say that entire afghanistan provinces like Ghazni, Kabul, Kandahar, all were the provinces of Bhaati rajputs! 


Here in this song, Pabuji - The Rajput king is leaving his kingdom by riding a horse (borrowed from Deval Chaarni - an avataar or Godess Durga), taking his baarat to another province, in order to marry the rajputaani from that province! While leaving he had promised Deval chaarni that he will come back to defend the kingdom and the cattles whenever she will call him.
Dewal chaarani (an avataar of Goddess durga), in order to test Pabuji, calls pabuji back to protect the cattles, during his marriage ritual was going on. 
Pabuji - the rajput king, left the HINDU-marriage ritual half by completing only 4 cimumabulations out of 7 around the agni-kund (fire) with his wife and came back to the kingdom on the same horse in order to protect the cattles!


Due to this reasons even today in western part of rajasthan I've heard that this tradition of the marriage ritual with only 4 circumabulations is still carried on!
